Use when evaluating technical stack choices.

```markdown
## Stack Evaluation

| Criteria                     | Weight | Stack A | Stack B | Stack C |
| ---------------------------- | ------ | ------- | ------- | ------- |
| Team familiarity             | 25%    | /10     | /10     | /10     |
| Time to MVP                  | 20%    | /10     | /10     | /10     |
| Scalability ceiling          | 15%    | /10     | /10     | /10     |
| Ecosystem/community support  | 15%    | /10     | /10     | /10     |
| Hiring pool availability     | 10%    | /10     | /10     | /10     |
| Long-term maintenance cost   | 10%    | /10     | /10     | /10     |
| Performance requirements met | 5%     | /10     | /10     | /10     |
| **Weighted Total**           | 100%   |         |         |         |
```

### Template 3: Feature Set Comparison

Use when comparing different feature scopes for MVP.

```markdown
## Feature Set Evaluation

| Criteria                     | Weight | Set A   | Set B   | Set C   |
| ---------------------------- | ------ | ------- | ------- | ------- |
| Core value delivery          | 30%    | /10     | /10     | /10     |
| Implementation feasibility   | 20%    | /10     | /10     | /10     |
| User learning curve          | 15%    | /10     | /10     | /10     |
| Competitive differentiation  | 15%    | /10     | /10     | /10     |
| Revenue potential            | 10%    | /10     | /10     | /10     |
| Testing complexity           | 10%    | /10     | /10     | /10     |
| **Weighted Total**           | 100%   |         |         |         |
```

### Default Weight Guidance

| Decision Type | Top 2 Criteria (50%+) | Secondary (30%) | Tertiary (20%) |
|---------------|----------------------|-----------------|----------------|
| Problem Angle | Root cause, Differentiation | User articulation, Market | Team, Validation |
| Stack Selection | Team familiarity, Time to MVP | Scalability, Ecosystem | Hiring, Maintenance |
| Feature Set | Core value, Feasibility | Learning curve, Differentiation | Revenue, Testing |

